- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the challenges of reweighting the estimator to avoid degeneracies in counterfactual learning, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method to improve the performance of a system using human feedback, which is a common approach in AI. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper also discusses the design of an easy-to-use interface to collect human feedback on semantic parses, which falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper mentions the use of stochastic gradient optimization, which is a common technique in information retrieval.
